=====================================================================
1. DEVICE CONNECTS TO ROUTER (DHCP PHASE)
=====================================================================

Jab device (laptop/mobile) router se connect karta hai,
to router DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol) ke through
network configuration assign karta hai.


                    ┌──────────────────────┐
                    │      ROUTER          │
                    │   (DHCP SERVER)      │
                    └──────────┬───────────┘
                               │
                               │ Assigns
                               ▼

                    ┌──────────────────────┐
                    │       LAPTOP         │
                    └──────────────────────┘


Example:

IP Address:
192.168.1.5

Gateway:
192.168.1.1

DNS Server:
192.168.1.1
OR
8.8.8.8 (Google DNS)

Subnet Mask:
255.255.255.0


---------------------------------------------------------------------
CAN TWO DEVICES CONNECTED TO SAME ROUTER HAVE SAME PRIVATE IP?
---------------------------------------------------------------------

NO.

Same local network ke andar:
do active devices ka same private IP nahi ho sakta.


❌ INVALID:

    Laptop:
    192.168.1.5

    Phone:
    192.168.1.5


Agar dono same IP use karein,
to network conflict ho jayega.

Isi wajah se DHCP ensure karta hai:
har connected device ko unique private IP mile.


HOWEVER:

Different routers/networks me same private IP possible hai.


✔ VALID:

    Home router mai Mobile ka IP:
    192.168.1.5

    Office router mai mobile ka IP:
    192.168.1.5


Ye valid hai because:
private IPs globally unique nahi hote.

Sirf local network ke andar unique hone chahiye.


