=====================================================================
SUBNET MASK AND GATEWAY ROLE
=====================================================================

Jab laptop ko kisi destination IP par packet bhejna hota hai,
to sabse pehle wo check karta hai:

"Kya ye destination mere local network (same subnet) me hai?"


                    ┌────────────────────┐
                    │  SUBNET MASK       │
                    │ decides:           │
                    │                    │
                    │ LOCAL ?            │
                    │ or                 │
                    │ OUTSIDE NETWORK ?  │
                    └────────────────────┘


Yahan subnet mask use hota hai.


---------------------------------------------------------------------
EXAMPLE
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Laptop IP:
    192.168.1.5

Subnet Mask:
    255.255.255.0


Is subnet mask ka meaning hai:

    192.168.1.xxx

wale devices same local network me hain.


To:

    192.168.1.2
    192.168.1.5
    192.168.1.100

same local network me hain.


But:

    142.250.xx.xx  (Google server IP)

same local network me nahi hai.


=====================================================================
CASE 1: DESTINATION SAME LOCAL NETWORK ME HAI
=====================================================================


                    SAME LOCAL NETWORK

    Laptop                        Mobile
 192.168.1.5  ───────────────▶ 192.168.1.7


Suppose:

Mobile bhi same router se connected hai.

Mobile IP:
    192.168.1.7


Ab laptop packet bhejna chahta hai:

    192.168.1.5
        ->
    192.168.1.7


Laptop subnet check karta hai aur dekhta hai:

    192.168.1.7

same subnet me hai because:

    192.168.1.xxx

same local network hai.


Ab laptop conclude karta hai:

"Destination local network me hi hai,
isliye gateway/router ki zarurat nahi hai."


Is case me:

- gateway use nahi hoga
- packet directly local network me bheja jayega


Laptop ko mobile ko packet bhejne ke liye mobile ka MAC address chahiye.


So laptop ARP broadcast bhejta hai:

    "Who has 192.168.1.7 ?
     Tell 192.168.1.5"


Mobile reply karta hai:

    "192.168.1.7 is me.
     My MAC is:
     XX:YY:ZZ"


NOW LAPTOP FRAME BHEJTA HAI


Ethernet/WiFi Frame:

    Destination MAC:
    Mobile MAC

    Source MAC:
    Laptop MAC


Inside IP Packet:

    Source IP:
    192.168.1.5

    Destination IP:
    192.168.1.7


=====================================================================
CASE 2: DESTINATION LOCAL NETWORK KE BAHAR HAI
=====================================================================


                    OUTSIDE NETWORK

    Laptop
 192.168.1.5
        │
        ▼
    Gateway / Router
     192.168.1.1
        │
        ▼
      INTERNET
        │
        ▼
  142.250.xx.xx


Ab suppose laptop Google server ko packet bhejna chahta hai:

    142.250.xx.xx


Laptop subnet check karta hai aur conclude karta hai:

    "Ye IP mere local network me nahi hai."


Ab laptop decide karta hai:

    "Packet ko gateway/router ke paas bhejna padega."


IMPORTANT:

Packet ka final destination IP change nahi hota.


Packet ke andar STILL likha hota hai:

    Destination IP:
    142.250.xx.xx

NOT:

    192.168.1.1


GATEWAY KA ROLE :

Gateway actually "next-hop" hota hai.

Matlab laptop internally sochta hai:

    "Ye packet ultimately Google ke liye hai,
     but us tak pahunchne ke liye pehle router ko dena padega,
     kyunki router hi internet tak rasta jaanta hai."


=====================================================================
DNS LOOKUP CASE ME SUBNET AUR GATEWAY KA ROLE
=====================================================================


                    CASE 1
         DNS SERVER = 192.168.1.1


Example:

DHCP ne DNS server diya:

    192.168.1.1


Ab laptop DNS request bhejna chahta hai:

    192.168.1.5
        ->
    192.168.1.1


Laptop subnet mask check karta hai aur dekhta hai:

    192.168.1.1

same local network me hai because:

    192.168.1.xxx

same subnet hai.


IS CASE ME KYA HOGA?

- destination local hai
- gateway use nahi hoga
- packet directly local network me bheja jayega


Laptop ko packet bhejne ke liye
destination MAC address chahiye.

IP address enough nahi hota
local Ethernet/WiFi communication ke liye.


So laptop ARP broadcast bhejta hai:

    "Who has 192.168.1.1 ?
     Tell 192.168.1.5"


Router bolta hai:

    "192.168.1.1 is me.
     My MAC is:
     AA:BB:CC:DD"


NOW LAPTOP FRAME BHEJTA HAI


Ethernet/WiFi Frame:

    Destination MAC:
    Router MAC

    Source MAC:
    Laptop MAC


Inside IP Packet:

    Source IP:
    192.168.1.5

    Destination IP:
    192.168.1.1


IMPORTANT UNDERSTANDING

Yahan router as gateway act nahi kar raha.

Yahan router simply ek local device ki tarah act kar raha hai.

Kyuki:

    192.168.1.1

same subnet me hai.


